cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SI 

This paper is about reducing the memory footprint of large-scale online learning methods, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses randomized counting, which is related to counting algorithms and data structures, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on memory usage and tradeoffs suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
